But he also claimed too much at times. The Irish do, it's part of the self-mythologizing. I was surprised recently to come across the place-name 'terfyn' twice in my own newly adopted parish in north Wales. I recognised the word immediately from the Heaney farm and from its roots in the Latin 'terminus'. Whatever he claimed to be, Heaney was also cross-referenced. After all, 'everywhere being nowhere who can claim one place more than another?'



